  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 28 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 10 high, 10 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 13 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK), Eindhoven (EIN/EHEH) and 23 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 4 airports changed status, led by David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Zayed (AUH/OMAA), Ben Gurion (TLV/LLBG) and 1 others.",
